Kylie Jenner (R) and Kendall Jenner attend the American Music Awards on November 22, 2015. File Photo by Jim Ruymen/UPI | License Photo

Kylie Jenner (R) and sister Kourtney Kardashian attend the InStyle and Warner Bros. Golden Globes after-party on January 10, 2016. File Photo by David Silpa/UPI | License Photo

Kylie Jenner attends the Harper's Bazaar Icons party on September 9, 2016. The reality star accompanied high school junior Albert Ochoa to his prom at Rio Americano High School in Sacramento, Calif., on Saturday. File Photo by Andrea Hanks/UPI | License Photo

April 10 (UPI) -- Kylie Jenner surprised high school students Saturday by showing up as their classmate's date to prom.

The 19-year-old reality star accompanied high school junior Albert Ochoa to his prom at Rio Americano High School in Sacramento, Calif., with friend Jordyn Woods, according to E! News.

Advertisement

Jenner shared a photo on Snapchat of herself and Woods traveling on a private jet before arriving at Tsakopoulos Library Galleria for the dance. The star wore a one-shoulder, blush-colored dress and a white corsage.

"TELL ME WHY MY BROTHER TOOK KYLIE JENNER TO PROM 2NIGHT !!!!!!!" Ochoa's sister, Selena Ochoa, excitedly tweeted.

Ochoa's friend Chayse Rothchild-Bruno told the Sacramento Bee someone on Jenner's staff had seen on social media that Ochoa was looking for a date. The star showed up after 10 p.m. to dance and take photos with Ochoa.

"Everyone started screaming, 'It's Kylie Jenner!'" Rothchild-Bruno recalled. "I think I was in denial, like no way is it Kylie Jenner. It was pretty crazy."

Several students, including Sam Adams, shared videos of Jenner on social media. The Keeping Up with the Kardashians star, who was homeschooled after the ninth grade, discussed her dream prom with Seventeen in 2013.

"I don't have a boyfriend, but I do really want that boyfriend prom experience," she said at the time. "I would want to go with someone who's not afraid, or doesn't think that he's too cool, to show up at my house with a rose corsage."

"It would be nice for the guy to come over and be respectful and nice while my mom takes prom pics," the star added.
